(5309, '_transient_dash_88ae138922fe95674369b1cb3d215a2b', '<div class=\"rss-widget\"><ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://wordpress.org/news/2021/11/the-month-in-wordpress-october-2021/\'>The Month in WordPress: October 2021</a> <span class=\"rss-date\">November 4, 2021</span><div class=\"rssSummary\">October 2021 brought a lot of new things to WordPress, from release updates to new versions of Gutenberg. More notably, in the latest episode of WP Briefing, Executive Director Josepha Haden reminded us about the importance of freedom in open source platforms like WordPress. Free speech has with it a lot of responsibility, just like [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div><div class=\"rss-widget\"><ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://gutenbergtimes.com/live-improving-development-tools-and-theme-revolution-weekend-edition-192/\'>Gutenberg Times: Life-improving development tools and Theme Revolution – Weekend Edition 192</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://wptavern.com/amp-has-irreparably-damaged-publishers-trust-in-google-led-initiatives?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=amp-has-irreparably-damaged-publishers-trust-in-google-led-initiatives\'>WPTavern: AMP Has Irreparably Damaged Publishers’ Trust in Google-led Initiatives</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://wptavern.com/patchstack-releases-free-security-plugin-its-red-team-found-over-1182-vulnerabilities-since-march?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=patchstack-releases-free-security-plugin-its-red-team-found-over-1182-vulnerabilities-since-march\'>WPTavern: Patchstack Releases Free Security Plugin, Its Red Team Found 1,182 Vulnerabilities Since March</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"rss-widget\"><ul></ul></div>', 'no'),
