(352, 4, '2016-03-23 22:37:11', '2016-03-24 06:37:11', '<h1>AUDITING</h1>\r\n<p class=\"highlight\">Omega\'s auditors assess your supply chain partners against proprietary, international and local regulations. Our service is flexible; we can just as simply adopt a proprietary standard as we can develop one in line with your precise requirements.</p>\r\nOffering a full spectrum of supply chain auditing services, Omega\'s dedicated teams of professionals, expert in their specific disciplines and local to the markets in which they operate, provide many of the world\'s best known brands and retailers with eyes and ears in the field.\r\n\r\nOmega\'s audit methodology is developed from our unparalleled experience in handling industry best practices within a multitude of product types from around the world.\r\n<h2>RESPONSIBLE SOURCING</h2>\r\nAn industry leader in the social compliance field, Omega performs more than 3,000 social compliance audits annually across China, South Asia, South East Asia, and The Middle East. Representing many of the world\'s most ethical companies, Omega provides a window into the working conditions across their global manufacturing base enabling our partners to make critical business decisions in complete confidence.\r\n\r\nHeadquartered in the heart of Asia, Omega understands that each market is different. Omega invests heavily in its auditing teams who are vastly knowledgeable, highly experienced, expert in international and local regulations as well as native in the requisite language(s) of their market. We are highly sensitive to local cultures and perform audits as sensitively as possible without disrupting your supplier relationships.\r\n\r\nOmega understands that the most daunting challenge your manufacturers face is not in understanding where their problems lie, but in how to resolve them efficiently and effectively. A different formula is needed. Omega is set apart from its competitors by a focus on corrective action planning and supplier remediation. Omega\'s approach is centered upon a real knowledge of the challenges, clear communications, a detailed corrective action plan agreed onsite and practical advice each step of the way.\r\n\r\nFor more information on how Omega can support your business please <strong><a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>.\r\n<h2>SUPPLY CHAIN SECURITY</h2>\r\nIn order to demonstrate compliance with international supply chain security standards, importers must continually assess their supply chains to identify, mitigate and eliminate potential security hazards as well as monitor ongoing improvements. Failure to comply with importer security requirements, such as C-TPAT and PIP, may result in Customs delaying your shipments or even having them seized at enormous cost to your business.\r\n\r\nOmega is an industry leader in the supply chain security field. We are expert at working with all supply chain partners, from manufacturers, warehouses, logistics providers to ports and perform in excess of 1,000 security audits each year across more than 20 countries worldwide. Omega has world-class account management experience; developing risk analyses and managing global supply chain security programs for some of the most prestigious importers into the United States and Canada.\r\n\r\nYour supply chain is more complicated than you might think. With a wide network of suppliers, some large, some small, some experienced and some new, spread over many countries, effectively assuring a secure and compliant supply chain is a daunting challenge. Omega\'s security expertise will guide you.\r\n\r\nFor more information on how Omega can support your business please <strong><a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>.\r\n<h2>COUNTRY OF ORIGIN DUE DILIGENCE</h2>\r\nShould your company be benefitting from reduced tariffs under the benefits of specific free trade agreements (FTAs), such as the arrangement between The EU and ASEAN, it is imperative that your merchandise is in compliance with all Customs requirements. Should Customs choose to examine your merchandise and determine that it is eligible for duty free benefits then you may be fined and your shipments delayed.\r\n\r\nTo mitigate this risk and to provide evidence of a rigorous due diligence process, Omega experts verify from where your supplier is manufacturing your merchandise as well as procuring the relevant raw materials.\r\n\r\nFor more information on how Omega can support your business please <strong><a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>.', 'Auditing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-23 22:37:11', '2016-03-24 06:37:11', '', 32, 'https://local.omega.com/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(353, 4, '2016-03-23 22:46:25', '2016-03-24 06:46:25', '<h1>Supply Chain Integrity</h1>\r\n<p class=\"highlight\">Fraud and corruption across supply chains is a serious risk and has enormous potential consequences to your business. Common corrupt practices include purchase orders being awarded to poorly qualified suppliers, factories with egregious ethical issues becoming part of your supply chain or defective shipments being passed by quality inspectors.</p>\r\nWhile these risks can never be eliminated it is imperative that you have the requisite controls in place across your business operations. Omega’s dedicated ethical monitoring team provides a broad range of integrity investigations services, such as conflicts of interest, bribery, and fraud, both internal and external, to companies who may not have the in-house resources to manage this risk themselves. Omega has unparalleled experience in developing and managing anti-corruption programs, programs which span more than 20 countries and a supply base in excess of 2,000 manufacturers.\r\n\r\nFor more information on how Omega can support your business please <strong><a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>.', 'Anti-Corruption', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '41-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-23 22:46:25', '2016-03-24 06:46:25', '', 41, 'https://local.omega.com/41-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(354, 4, '2016-03-23 22:47:35', '2016-03-24 06:47:35', '<h1>Supply Chain Integrity</h1>\n<p class=\"highlight\">Fraud and corruption across supply chains is a serious risk and has enormous potential consequences to your business. Common corrupt practices include purchase orders being awarded to poorly qualified suppliers, factories with egregious ethical issues becoming part of your supply chain or defective shipments being passed by quality inspectors.</p>\nWhile these risks can never be eliminated it is imperative that you have the requisite controls in place across your business operations. Omega’s dedicated ethical monitoring team provides a broad range of integrity investigations services, such as conflicts of interest, bribery, and fraud, both internal and external, to companies who may not have the in-house resources to manage this risk themselves. Omega has unparalleled experience in developing and managing anti-corruption programs, programs which span more than 20 countries and a supply base in excess of 2,000 manufacturers.\n\nFor more information on how Omega can support your business please <strong><a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>.', 'Integrity', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '41-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-23 22:47:35', '2016-03-24 06:47:35', '', 41, 'https://local.omega.com/41-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(355, 4, '2016-03-23 22:47:56', '2016-03-24 06:47:56', '<h1>Supply Chain Integrity</h1>\r\n<p class=\"highlight\">Fraud and corruption across supply chains is a serious risk and has enormous potential consequences to your business. Common corrupt practices include purchase orders being awarded to poorly qualified suppliers, factories with egregious ethical issues becoming part of your supply chain or defective shipments being passed by quality inspectors.</p>\r\nWhile these risks can never be eliminated it is imperative that you have the requisite controls in place across your business operations. Omega’s dedicated ethical monitoring team provides a broad range of integrity investigations services, such as conflicts of interest, bribery, and fraud, both internal and external, to companies who may not have the in-house resources to manage this risk themselves. Omega has unparalleled experience in developing and managing anti-corruption programs, programs which span more than 20 countries and a supply base in excess of 2,000 manufacturers.\r\n\r\nFor more information on how Omega can support your business please <strong><a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>.', 'Integrity', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '41-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-23 22:47:56', '2016-03-24 06:47:56', '', 41, 'https://local.omega.com/41-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(356, 4, '2016-03-23 22:49:20', '2016-03-24 06:49:20', '<h1>Supply Chain Integrity</h1>\r\n<p class=\"highlight\">Fraud and corruption across supply chains is a serious risk and has enormous potential consequences to your business. Common corrupt practices include purchase orders being awarded to poorly qualified suppliers, factories with egregious ethical issues becoming part of your supply chain or defective shipments being passed by quality inspectors.</p>\r\nWhile these risks can never be eliminated it is imperative that you have the requisite controls in place across your business operations. Omega’s dedicated ethical monitoring team provides a broad range of integrity investigations services, such as conflicts of interest, bribery, and fraud, both internal and external, to companies who may not have the in-house resources to manage this risk themselves. Omega has unparalleled experience in developing and managing anti-corruption programs, programs which span more than 20 countries and a supply base in excess of 2,000 manufacturers.\r\n\r\nFor more information on how Omega can support your business please <strong><a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>.', 'Integrity', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '41-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-23 22:49:20', '2016-03-24 06:49:20', '', 41, 'https://local.omega.com/41-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(357, 4, '2016-03-23 23:11:14', '2016-03-24 07:11:14', '<h1>About Us</h1>\r\n<p class=\"highlight\">Every day many of the world\'s most trusted companies put their faith in Omega to ensure the integrity of their global supply chains as they endeavor to work with partners who are ethical, secure and free from corrupt practices.</p>\r\nOmega goes beyond monitoring. We focus upon thorough assessments, comprehensive investigations, full disclosure and effective remediation. We strive to ensure that all parties, from manufacturers, trading entities, logistics providers, brands and retailers have full transparency over their supply chain partners, product and associates. We enable our clients to understand any shortcomings then provide them with the expertise to remediate effectively allowing them to operate their supply chains with complete confidence.', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-23 23:11:14', '2016-03-24 07:11:14', '', 8, 'https://local.omega.com/8-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(359, 4, '2016-04-05 01:15:07', '2016-04-05 09:15:07', 'Chinese supply chains can be particularly murky.  Where the Purchase Order is placed and the product manufactured is often a different location. Suppliers often run multiple manufacturing sites and, in fact, many subcontract manufacturing to a separate business entity offering them the greatest margin\r\n\r\nThe greatest risk is when factories then subcontract a process, or entire production, to another factory without disclosing it. The worst case scenario being a company learning, either through the media or other sources that, not only are their products manufactured at factories with egregious workplace violations, but they were unaware that they were doing business with these manufacturers in the first place.\r\n\r\nIn Omega’s experience the majority of Chinese factories subcontract at least one production process to a separate, undisclosed, manufacturer.  Within the garment industry, for example, it is the norm to subcontract washing to another factory.  Local governments in China disincentive factories in the industrial zones from having this highly polluting process onsite by requiring complex permits and expensive treatment plants. As such, factories typically outsource this process to sites, further inland, with the requisite technology and under less scrutiny from local officials.  Labor intensive and requiring specialized skills, the embroidery process is typically outsourced also.\r\n\r\nUnauthorized subcontracting poses serious challenges.  Omega recommends that brands and retailers push for transparency by requiring their factories to disclose subcontracting before any orders are placed.  The issue though is how do companies approach their Tier II factories from a responsible sourcing perspective?  Rarely exposed to auditing, operating on even finer profit margins, and with even weaker commercial relationships, these factories are not well placed to meet typical responsible sourcing requirements.\r\n\r\nJust last month, while scheduling an assessment at a factory in China, Omega was asked for some informal advice.  The factory was working with a separate client who permits subcontracting on the basis that the Tier II site produces a recent audit report verifying that it meets its responsible sourcing standards.  While the approach is commendable, the policy lacked the pragmatism to be effective.  The site hadn’t been audited before and, due to production lead times, it wasn’t possible to organize an audit or identify a new subcontractor.  Further, even if an audit was performed the Tier II factory almost certainly wouldn’t meet the client’s standard.  The factory was concerned about losing the order, and asked if Omega knew of an alternative site. This suggests that if it couldn’t identity a compliant one it may even resort to attempting to bribe the client’s auditor.\r\n\r\nWhile attempted bribery is completely unacceptable, Omega did sympathize with the supplier’s predicament. Perhaps the most practical solution would be to hold Tier II sites to a less comprehensive standard where they are assessed for zero tolerance issues only. Another solution would be for brands and retailers to collaborate around a number of Tier II embroidery factories, for example? With more stable commercial relationships, these sites would then be in a better position to make the requisite investment in workplace conditions driving responsible sourcing and supply chain transparency from the ground up.\r\n\r\nOmega has vast experience in managing compliance programs across subcontractors. Should you require information on our services do please <a href=\"https://local.omega.com/contact/\">contact us</a>.', 'Case Study: Unauthorized Subcontracting in Chinese Supply Chains', 'The majority of Chinese factories subcontract at least one production process to a separate, undisclosed, manufacturer.  This poses a significant risk to responsible sourcing programs.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'subcontracting', '', '', '2016-04-21 19:38:03', '2016-04-22 03:38:03', '', 0, 'https://local.omega.com/?p=359', 0, 'post', '', 0),
